<TrainingDetailsVTwo ID="x68536" Name="A-Z Index" Layout="default-training_v2.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">A-Z Index</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Automatically generates an alphabetized index of pages, sorted by Title, and grouped by the first letter.</Abstract><TrainingImage type="imagefile" label="Page Type Image" hidden="false" readonly="false" required="false" Expanded="true" AlternateText="" Border="" HSpace="" VSpace="" Width="300" Height="458" Alignment="">Internal_Use/Ingeniux_Training/Template Thumbnails/azsiteindex.jpg</TrainingImage><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<h3>Proper Use</h3>
<p>As a site-map of a particular area or sub-site. For example, a college would use one of these to index all pages in their site.</p>
<p>Pages can be marked for "no index" and they will not appear in the index page.</p>
<h3>Audience</h3>
<p>Everyone</p>
<h3>Intended Authors&nbsp;</h3>
<p>All advanced authors (editors).</p>
<h3>Instructions</h3>
<ol>
<li>Enter a <a href="x17231.xml">title</a> and an <a href="x17584.xml">abstract</a> immediately. These are required elements that, if left empty, prevent you from saving your page.</li>
<li>Create the&nbsp;introduction paraghraph for the A-Z index in the <a href="x17232.xml">Body Copy</a>. The body area is 650px wide.</li>
<li>You will need to select a CMS Page or folder that contain all the pages you wish to list in the A-Z Index page. <ol>
<li>Place it's ID number (x??????) in the "Start Page" text field in the <a href="x18250.xml">Index Element</a>.</li>
<li>Set the "Type" menu to Children.</li>
<li>Set Max Depth value.</li>
</ol> </li>
<li>Deside on what CMS Pages&nbsp; you wish to not include in the A-Z Index.<ol>
<li>Create a <a href="x24333.xml">Taxonomy Navigation</a> of the CMS Pages you wish to remove for the list.</li>
<li>Include the Taxonomy Navigation into the <a href="x18249.xml">Excluded Category</a>.</li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<p>A sample A-Z Index page is available in the Page Type Demos folder (xID: x9575).</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
